What are Frozen Chicken Paws?
Frozen chicken paws are processed poultry byproducts that are cleaned, graded, frozen, and distributed for culinary, food processing, and pet food applications. Rich in collagen and protein, they are widely consumed across Asian and African cuisines in soups, stews, braised dishes, dim sum, snacks, and collagen-rich food products. Frozen chicken paws are also increasingly utilized in premium pet treats due to their nutritional value and natural composition.

Modern frozen chicken paws processing integrates advanced technologies including:

·         High-efficiency Processing & Grading Systems for consistent product quality

·         IQF (Individual Quick Freezing) Technology for freshness preservation

·         Vacuum Packaging Solutions for extended shelf life

·         Cold Chain Logistics for safe international transportation

·         HACCP & Halal Certified Processing Facilities for global export compliance

·         Automated Quality Inspection Systems for food safety assurance

By providing affordable, high-protein poultry products with long shelf life and broad culinary versatility, frozen chicken paws help processors, exporters, retailers, and foodservice operators meet growing global demand while supporting efficient utilization of poultry byproducts.

